    "body": "<p>The Problem is simple. You will be given n integers .Find an arrangement of these n integers so that summation of the absolute differences between adjacent elements is maximized. Suppose n = 4 and the given integers are &lt;4 2 1 5&gt;. The re-arrangement &lt;2 5 1 4&gt; yields the maximum summation.\nFor this arrangement, sum = abs(2-5) + abs(5-1) + abs(1-4) = 3+4+3 = 10.\nOf all the 24 different arrangements of the above list, you won\u2019t get any summation whose value exceeds 10. We will call this value, 10, the \"Interesting list sum\".\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n</p><p>The Input will consist of number of test cases. Each case consists of a line that starts with n. n will be greater than 1 and smaller than 51, followed by n non-negative integers separated by a single space. None of the elements of the given list will exceed 1000. Terminate the input with n=0.\n<br />\n<h3>Output</h3>\n</p><p>For each case, output the \"Interesting list sum\".\n\n<h3>Example</h3>\n\n<pre>\n<b>Input:</b>\n4 4 2 1 5\n4 1 1 1 1\n2 10 1\n0\n<b>Output:</b>\n10\n0\n9\n</pre></p>",
